quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  100,10,"And that within the breasts is obtained,<sup foot_note=197802>1</sup>",footnotes:197802:1
  101,1,"The Striking Calamity -"
  101,2,"What is the Striking Calamity?"
  101,3,"And what can make you know what is the Striking Calamity?"
  101,4,"It is the Day when people will be like moths, dispersed,<sup foot_note=197804>1</sup>",footnotes:197804:1
  101,5,"And the mountains will be like wool, fluffed up.<sup foot_note=197805>1</sup>",footnotes:197805:1
  101,6,"Then as for one whose scales are heavy [with good deeds],"
  101,7,"He will be in a pleasant life."
  101,8,"But as for one whose scales are light,"
  101,9,"His refuge<sup foot_note=197806>1</sup> will be an abyss.<sup foot_note=197807>2</sup>",footnotes:197806:1,footnotes:197807:2
  101,10,"And what can make you know what that is?"
  102,1,"Competition in [worldly] increase diverts you"
  102,2,"Until you visit the graveyards.<sup foot_note=197808>1</sup>",footnotes:197808:1
  102,3,"No! You are going to know."
  102,4,"Then, no! You are going to know."
  102,5,"No! If you only knew with knowledge of certainty...<sup foot_note=197809>1</sup>",footnotes:197809:1
  102,6,"You will surely see the Hellfire."
  102,7,"Then you will surely see it with the eye of certainty.<sup foot_note=197810>1</sup>",footnotes:197810:1
  102,8,"Then you will surely be asked that Day about pleasure.<sup foot_note=197811>1</sup>",footnotes:197811:1